column2: Most bokoblin don't have the patient to raise horses themselves so often they either break in wild horses, or die tring, or steal already domesticated horses from human settlements.
A number of natural caves are inhabited by Hinox.
A number of natural caves are inhabited by Lynol.

The trial zones are a series of ancient caverns each houseing a unique environment, when they were built is a mystery and to this day they are in good conditions. However they may need some repairs to restore access to the caverns.
Here knights face off against one another in jousting tournaments and other chivalrous competitions
Housecarl are the traditional body guards of the ho_ho nobility, often armed with axes and heavy armor.
The koridain Goldpikes are renowned for their skills with pikes and often gold colored cuiresses.
It is here that fearsome war elephants are raised and trained
Among the Morians the longbow and archery are things of pride, usually most Morians are trained in archery first and then other forms of combat.
It is here that rangers, infantry skilled in combat in woodland combat, are trained
It is here that individuals skilled in swordsmanship are trained and housed.
Port Town has been a haven for mercenaries since it was settled by humans. Most savy nobles can easily find a way to exploit these people in times of need

Ordon Herdsmen are all skilled horsemen many of whom are recruited from skilled goat herders and hands. When called to battle their tactics reflects that of  herding Ordon Goats and often said to be more stuborn than the goats they once herded.

The Chilfos Warriors of the Frozen Isle are renowned for the shinning scale armor and polar bear furs. Every warrior obtained their furs after slaying an Icy Plain Bear armed with only an axe and some Icy Plain Bird meat.

The magic enclaves of Kasuto are places of learning where one can learn how to perfom magic. Most however do not learn enough magic before they become too old to fight so must use their magic from behind the frontlines.
The Rivermen are heavily armed militia originating in Saria.
The Crow Warriors are a cult of horse bound warriors from the Eldin Plateaus. Most warriors ride into battle adorned in leather armor decorated with bones and feathers.

The sapper armory is a massive reinforced building, usually far away from the main building, housing large amounts of explosives. Those that use these weapons are usually carefully trained in making and detonating the contents
It is here that stone soldiers, large golem like warriors are built and maintained.
The Sheikah Spearmasters are renowned for their use of spears and polearms.
Most gerudo live in fortresses cities frequently are little more than fortresses with larger markets. It is in blockhouses that most gerudo live
The gerudo are proud of their horses and prefer to fight from afar when they can.
After centuries of inhabitation by the wind tribe the walls and ground have been saturated with wind magic to the point that the very land begins to float above ground.
With the aid of piccori the Wind Tribe can create complex machanised warriors
An additional keep in which the castles lords keeps and trains his mage servents
It is here that the keaton warriors are taught more advanced techniques.
It is here that young warriors are taught advance combat manuvers
The anouki are one of the rare none human races capable of magic, however their magic is narrow, they can only freeze water. However a skilled shaman is capable of freezing any amount of water.
The lokomo warriors sometime remove their arms in place of mechanical constructs to be used in war. These half machine warriors are even fierce warriors after their replacement.
The elite guard are made up of those that have proven their loyalty to the house family and are often attached to guard family members and valuble guests.
The papuchian sailbows are large bows made of the palm trees from papuchia, despite their size their weight is that of a Morian longbow.
A large keep like stable in which houses pegasuses.
A larger stable in which camels are housed.
The Zora Knights typically go into battle wearing heavy coral armor, it is here where they hold racing compatitions and melees.
The Sea Zora are very protective of their coasts. When called upon most peasents go to war with fishbone bows and coral spears.
The Zola are fiercly territorial of their rivers. Any who comes close to the shores are met with hordes of zolas armed with any weapon they can obtain.
Berserkers are common in some cultures frequently they go into battle with little regard for their own saftey usually wielding multiple weapons or one large weapon.
The Knights of twili are very similar to that of Hyrule but do to the lack of ridable animals in the Twilight Realm most go to battle on foot.
The art of creating shadow beast has been outlawed by everysingle tribe in the Twilight Realm however certain cults practice this forbiden and perverse art in secret.
The Loftwing have borne mailed armored warriors for mellinia. However most loftwing require large areas to sleep and the practicle is making a large tower to house them.
The Lynel are a mutation of the lynol most lynol however are little more than berserkers raging through enemy ranks.
The Girrin have an abnormally large number of individuals with magic abilities, most however require a instrument to use this magic.
A hold over from the days of Skyloft these dojos teach children and adults advanced sword techniques.
A common farm with crops consisting of wheat and pumpkins, along with a few cuccos.
A medium farm with  crops consisting of wheat and pumpkins, with several large pastures for cows.
A large farm  with crops consisting of wheat and pumpkins, with a central horse coral.
The farm grows Gasha trees which seem to grow magical items.
A small ordonion farm growing wheat and ordonion pumpkins
A ordonion farm growing wheat and ordonion pumpkins, in addition they have a few small herds of ordon goats
A ordonion farm growing large fields of wheat and having several herds of ordonion goats.
A seperate district in which caters to clothes making primarily for the rich.
A large orchard given over to raising silkwarm.
This city houses a tower given over to documenting the stars.
Spread throughout the city are a number of blockhouses in which most citizens live in. Each family has an individual apartment but in times of war can be used in defense.
After centuries of inhabitation by the wind tribe the walls and ground have been saturated with wind magic to the point that the very land begins to float above ground.
A farm that has been carved into the mountains and built up allowing for crops to be farmed.
A library containing both arcane and munday books hosting classes on the weekends
A school which teaches both the non-magical and magical citizens.
A school which teaches those capable of magic advanced forms of magic.
A district containing large vats of water in which shamans create mega ice. The ice can also be turned into arrow heads during war, allowing the arrows to break through armor.
Many Shacks situated around a body of water.
The fishing industry is more organized.
The fishing industry has now started raising fish on a large scale.
A seperate district devoted to growing Zora coral on an industrial scale.
The district is given over to musical entertainment, street and theater.
In the back alley of the markets most of the guards are paid off and the money eventually makes it to the stop to avoid crackdowns.
In this district guards never patrol and one can buy almost anything.
It is here that any who have the money can enroll their children into the acadamy in hopes of recieving knighthood.
The Skyloft pumpkin is capable of being grown in any type of dirt, it also is delicious.
A fortified building in most of the well trained moblins live.
A fortified building in which the poorly trained moblins live, primarily trained for attacking enemy positions before battle
Poorly made structures, usually of wood or twigs, in which the lowest ranked bokoblins live, often going into battle with whatever they can grab, usually parts of their homes.
A poorly made set of structures that can double as lookout towers and archery rangers, in which the most accurate bokoblins live.
A building in which most of the well trained bokoblins live, often going to battle with stolen weapons or crudely made metal weapons.
A fortified building in which those bulblin that display skill with clubs and melee weapons usually live.
A structure in which the bulblin expected to guard camps live.
A well fortified pen in which bulbos are raised.
Little more than a collection of shacks that cling to the side of the castle's walls. Most of the inhabitants are non-blin slaves and the weakest of blins.
Poorly made and highly flammible section of the city in which most of the moblin criminals come from.
The bokoblin slums, usually made of mud or twigs, where most of the bokoblin thieves come from
A ring of sod buildings in which most of the bulblin bandit gangs stay when they aren't attacking others.
A poorly made town in which most of the blin and slaves live.
A moblin camp made up of the warrior caste of moblins.
A poorly made camp in which most of the bokoblin warriors live.
A gathering of hide yurts in which most of the bulblin warriors live.
Large herds of bulbos used to breed better mounts for the bulblin warriors.
A building in which books are housed and offers free literacy education to all citizens.
A building in which any child under 16 may recieve basic education.
A large complex which offers education to citizens no matter their position depending on their wealth.
The city has developed a large open central area for which most items can be bought and sold.
Along the street to the market square is lined with shops.
The area surrounding the market town is dominated by stores and the apartments of those that work these stores.
A number of farms mainly growing crops dot the area around the holding.
A number of farms primarily raising cuccos dot the holding in addition to traditional farms.
Several large ranches raising cattle can be found around this holding.
A tent has been set aside in order to make potions for the treatment of ailments.
A coral built to contain the clan's cattles and other livestock.
A series of messanger posts lay between the various realm clans and holdings.
A heavily fortified building in which most of the combat skilled lfos live.
Metal Scales are the battle hardened warriors of the lfos, often going to battle with plate armor.
A large reinforced pen containing the castle's helmasaurus mounts.
The darkhammers are a rare strain of lizalfos typically much larger and bulkier than lizalfos, often going into battle with thick metal armor and blunt weapons.
The Draco are a rare red fire breathing strain of aeralfos.
A communal hatchery for all of the cities lfos. The building is designed to ensure that as many hatchlings reach maturity as possible.
A series of interconnected buildings that house the cities warrior class.
The cities trained elite warriors often tasked with guarding communities and ensuring conflict doesn't rise to bloodshed.
The city has a number of camps and buildings dedicated to capturing and killing animals for food.
The city has carefully cared for several areas insuring only the best sources of meat survive to adulthood.
The city has developed a number of large open areas into raising meat cattle.
An area has been cleared away and made into an earthen mound to insure that as many lfos reach maturity.
A number of clans are solely devoted to fighting those members rarely perform anyother task but fighting.
A number of clans have devoted themselves to hunting, in times of war however they lend their bows to fighting.
The Helmasaurus are the prized mounts of the dinolfos.
It is here that every King and Queen of Hyrule is burried, surrounded by the unnamed dead of hyrulean soldiers.
The ancient crypts of the Wind Kings. The feeling of lost is said to affect everyone.
A sealed room or diminsion in which is said to house the triforce and the mastersword.
The ancient guardian Mazaal inhabits the last bastion of the Wind Tribe.
A sacred room in which the door to the Minish world is housed, only children may enter and even see the door. To others it appears to be a masterly crafted stainglass windows.
A pool of water stands in this location, for some reason minor fairies seem to be in abundance. These fairies often appear to heal anyone nearby, those injured in battle or those that are sick.
Little more than a pit of sand in which the lowest and non-sentient stal are held when not fighting.
A former barracks littered with remains of the former warriors.
Once the kennel for the castle's hunting hound, now haunted by the stitched together remain of animals.
Little more than a pit in which remains are tossed to later be reanimated or used to repair destroyed soldiers.
A room or just a pit in which the mumified remains of humanoids are kept.

A multi headed serpent species that once inhabited the grasslands of what would become the Sea of Sand. While they are now extinct their remains are unusually easy to reanimate, they once would form balls and hibernate when pray was hard to find.
Their exact origin has been lost to history, all that is known is that once these child sized humanoids served the Ikanan armies as their main fighting infantry.

The Ikanan Armie's main human soldiers, during the rein of the Ikanan Empire these humans and sometime large monster like creatures served as the elite soldiers and made up the quality that the Stalchild soldier's quantity left lacking.
Little more than a hole in the ground in which the remains of damaged ikanan soldiers are tossed in to repair themselves, how they do this is subject to many grissly ghost stories.
A building given over to preparing bodies to be stalfos.
Piles of bones and sand litters the city. When called upon the bone piles reanimate.
Once the city guard now these creatures roam the town looking guarding the grave city against life.
Once the cities doctors now these creatures use magic and material to repair damaged stalfos.
The graves of the commoners when reanimated they use whatever they can get their hands on for weapons.
Once the graves of the nobles and well known warriors. Now they serve in death.
The main cause of the undead curse the phantoms are usually those that died horribly or were cursed.
The mass graves for the stalchildren thrown in with little care.
Once the graves of the well known warriors, often entombed with their armor and weapons.

The Initiates are the lowest ranked members of the Darknut society, they are either low born children or subjugated citizens. Their only hope of advancing is to survive long enough to be promoted to a legionairy.

The Legionairy is the main type of soldier in the darknut legions. Often coming from the upper classes, those that can pay to forge their armor and sword or those that have survived long enough to be deemed strong enough to be a noble.
The heart of the castle's commerce. Any and all items one needs to obtain can be obtained here.
A camp has surrounded the castle made up of those subjugated people that are skilled in the bow and horse.
Those of knight cultures are expected to send a portion of their soldiers to serve their lord's lord.
The Auxilary are the lowest ranked of the city dwelling Darknuts. They are expected to protect the order of the city.
The armored Cohorts of the cities are often made up of those Auxilary have performed beyond their expected duties, those disenfranchised nobles, and the dishonored legionairy.
In the center of the market area is a large arena that serves as the focal point for entertainment and commerce.
The Judicars take all followers of the Code no matter their rank or physical ailments, those members that are physically capable are taught both the Codes and how to use them in combat.
The Judicars are the warrior-priests of the Code.
A deep ditch has been carved into the ground.
A number of bombflowers have been planted around the battle field.
Set into eatch Tower or section of walls are large funnels that run off of them. During sieges the defenders push large spherical boulders down, sending them crashing into the enemy encampments.
Said to have been invented by a Hylian Martial Genius the Groosinator is a lever opperated catapult capable of hurling large explosives. Usually operated on a track to increase it's manuveribility.
The once empty ditch has been filled with lava.
Those gorons take joy in fighting tend to spend their time with like minded individuals.

Bombflowers are a unique plant that only grows naturally in mountains and rocky soil. The goron main use for them is to speed up mining and harvisting their food source, minerals. However during times of war a strong goron arm can throw these flowers frightingly far.
Those gorons that have devoted their very lives to fighting and defending their homes go to war clad in tasty metals and armed with hammers, picks, and halbard like weapons.
The goron are capable of curling into balls and rolling quickly. Those gorons that enjoy racing often create tracks around their homes. During times of war they will put their speed to use.
Gorons are skilled at finding lava veins. Often they will create hotsprings from these veins. These serve as a wellspring of knowledge and bonding.
The Gorons of Death Mountain have an unusual afinity for warfare, by goron standards. Often even their lowest troops go to war with a pic or a hammer.

The Gorons of the Crenal Mountain have shown an affinity for the use of long poles, said to have been learned from their ancient neighbors during the Hylia War. During combat these thick poles can be swung with horrifying force.

The Goron of Cucco Mountain are usually some of the most peaceful gorons but some of them when they experience the heat of battle give into a berserk rage that makes even the more war like Death Mountain gorons take pause.
During peaceful times the Wardancers entertain the lord of the holding with elaborate dances, but when war breaks out these goron put their agility and swiftness to use.
The subrosians of Cucco Mountain have managed to tame the ancestral enemy of the goron, the dodongo to use as cavalry.
Subrosians usually spend their entire lives underground, creating tunnels and new caverns when needed. When called to battle most subrosians are willing to go to war with their trusty picks.
The city guard keep order in the city and defend it during wars.
Little more than an open air quary where the goron harvest rocks to eat.
A series of mines work spread through the mountains.
The city has cultivated large amounts of bombflowers.
The gorons of Death Mountain take pride in strength.The most favored game is Goron Wrestling. Two contestetants enter a ring and must push the other out of the ring.
The gorons of the Grenal Mountains have always stood on the brink of major trade routes. Because of this trade has become a very valuble part of their culture.
The gorons of the Rolling Ridge value agility.
The Cucco Goron are well known for their crafting of exquisite and intricate pieces of jewlery rivaling even that of the Gemlanders.
The goron of Goro mountain have preserved the art of crafting remarkably sharp and durable Steel, which was last seen before the Hylia War.
Because of the Subrosian use of lava in forging they are able make stronger metal weapons, rivaling even the Goro Metal.
A deep ditch has been carved into the ground.
A number of bombflowers have been planted around the battle field.
Set into eatch Tower or section of walls are large funnels that run off of them. During sieges the defenders push large spherical boulders down, sending them crashing into the enemy encampments.
Said to have been invented by a Hylian Martial Genius the Groosinator is a lever opperated catapult capable of hurling large explosives. Usually operated on a track to increase it's manuveribility.
The once empty ditch has been filled with lava.
It is here that priests that feel the call to arms train.

Little more than a pool of lava. Among gorons those exhibit an unusual amount of religious fervor seemingly sprot volcanic hot spots, eventually these spots harden their skin, but also gives them back problems later in life.
The settlment is mostly above ground surrounded by reinforced earthen and stone dome.
The settlment has mostly moved underground.
The upper tunnels are lined with traps and fortifications.
The settlment now is deep underground.
The central cave in which the gorons train and prepare for war.
A large open field or cave in which the gorons test who has the stronger throwing arm.
A roughly smoothed area track in which goron practice racing.
Mad scrubs are the basic soldiers of the deku, typically they focuse on ranged attacks.
The olden Mad scrubs leaves turn orange, red, and yellow and their bark hardens.
The lily deku are an unusual breed. They are lighter than most deku and are capable of gliding.

The "Mad" Scrubs are born warrior most are born with the ability to shoot, seeds or what they eat. They are however extremly territorial against non-scrubs so most live in a large cleared out area dotted with deku flowers for them to make their dens under.
The Totem scrubs are an unusual breed of Deku scrub, which have a segmented body. Most Totem Scrubs live in tunnel networks underneath the totem grove.
Mad scrubs are the main warrior breed of deku.
When the Mad Scrubs grow old their leaves turn the color of fall leaves and their bark harden.
A flower strewn clearing in which deku flowers grow.
The races created by Demise often have a easy time finding a reason to fight. What more reason does one need to fight than land.
The races created by Demise often have a easy time finding a reason to fight. What more reason does one need to fight than land.
The human tribes have always had a low respect of the races of monsters. Takeing land from the monsters is usually enough justification for a war.
Often ambitious or mad Hylians have justified wars by the fact that the Hylians are the goddesses chosen people.
was abandoned in the wild at a very young age by $KILLER$
was gored to death by a bulbos on the order of $KILLER$

column2: The title Biggoron is given to an individual who is the largest in his tribe, usually towering above all other gorons.
The title Midgoron is given to an individual who is the second largest in his tribe, usually only shorter than the biggoron.
A title traditionally given to those that have performed their duties well beyond expectations, usually acts of bravery in the face of certain death. Usually given to one no matter their rank.
The title Immun is usually given to those who perform extra duties, whether it is a duty that is usually beneath or above their rank.
The Imagifer is the title given to the one who carries the Dox's Legion's Standard or an image of the Dox in the case of the more vein Dox.
The title of mighty is given to the strongest or most skilled with the sword. There are cases when it is given to someone shown to be extremly skilled in tactics.
